<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sourdough-waff-cakes" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Sourdough Pancakes &amp; Waffles</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup milk</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup (or more) sourdough starter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>1 teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 tablespoon brown sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>1 \frac{1}{2}</m> cups flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 eggs</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon baking soda</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>Water to adjust thickness of batter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>Blueberries, bananas, or other appropriate fruit for pancakes (optional)</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Melt butter in a pan and add milk.  Heat to warm.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mix starter, salt, brown sugar, flour, and butter/milk mixture and mix to form a thick batter.  Let it stand at room temperature for 8-14 hours.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mix in eggs and baking soda.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Add water so the batter is thick or thin enough for you.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Cook on the griddle with fruit or waffle iron not with fruit.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          The original recipe called for 1 cup starter.  I use a lot more than that with the same recipe, and I have been happy with the results.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          I make pancakes with either blueberries or sliced bananas.  I add the fruit to the batter right after I put it on the griddle and cover it with batter so it doesn't burn when I flip the pancakes.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>